Q9. Declare a constant and display it.
Answer
pl
Copy code
DECLARE
    c_pi CONSTANT NUMBER := 3.14159;
BEGIN
    DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Value of Pi: ' || c_pi);
END;
ðŸ”Ÿ Using Boolean Variable
Q10. Use a Boolean variable in PL/SQL.
Answer
plsql
Copy code
DECLARE
    is_valid BOOLEAN := TRUE;
BEGIN
    IF is_valid THEN
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Valid');
    ELSE
        DBMS_OUTPUT.PUT_LINE('Invalid');
    END IF;
END;
